<HTMLTextAreaElementSetCustomValidity>
<summary>
The <strong><c>setCustomValidity()</c></strong> method of the <see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement"/> interface sets the custom validity message for the {{htmlelement("textarea")}} element. Use the empty string to indicate that the element does <strong>not</strong> have a custom validity error.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea">textarea</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.Validity"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.CheckValidity"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.ReportValidity"/><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">Form validation</see>.<br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Extensions/Forms/Form_validation">Learn: Client-side form validation</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Constraint_validation">Guide: Constraint validation</see><br/>-CSS <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:valid">:valid</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:invalid">:invalid</see> pseudo-classes<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTextAreaElement/setCustomValidity"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<returns>None (<see cref="Undefined"/>).</returns>
</HTMLTextAreaElementSetCustomValidity>
